<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7069> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7069" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sumner questions the correctness of Livy's statement (29.11.12) that this Lucius was elected and served as curule aedile in absence in 205 (he was then proconsul in Spain, MRR 1.302). Sumner would identify him with L. Cornelius Lentulus Caudinus (212), curule aedile in 209 (see MRR 1.286), but keep him consul in 199, while attributing the curule aedileship of 205 to his younger brother Publius (214), who became praetor in 203 (MRR 1.311). See Orators 140, and stemma, 143, and Arethusa 3, 1970, 89. Two brothers remain as curule aediles together in 205, but not the same two as in MRR 1.302. R. C. Knapp, Aspects of the Roman Experience in Iberia, 206-100 B.C 91, note 18, accepts Livy's text. Note that C. Cornelius Cethegus (88), procos. in Spain 201-200 (Liv. 30.41.4-5) received a successor when elected aed. cur. for 199 in absence (31.50.11).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2608> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2608" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A. Postumius Albinus (Luscus) succeeded L. Cornelius Lentulus. Liv. 42.10.6. On Lentulus, see 213, note 8; on Postumius, Münzer, Bull. Com., 67 (1939) 27-30; Lübker, no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2049> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2049" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to arbitrate differences between Antiochus and Ptolemy (Liv. 33.39.1); went with other Legates (see below) to treat with Antiochus at Lysimacheia (Polyb. 18.49.3; Liv. 33.39.2, and 41.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2048> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2048" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The need for a man of seniority and distinction for this commission suggests that he was Lentulus, the Consul of 199." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1997> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1997" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His command in Gaul was prorogued until the coming of the Consul with a new army (Liv. 32.8.3, and 26.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1957> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1957" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.49.12; 32.2.6, 7.1 and 8, and 8.3; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 452f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Cornelius' province was Italy, but he went to Gaul after Baebius' defeat (Liv. 32.1.2-3 and 7.6-8). Villius was assigned Macedonia (Liv. 32.1.2-3), where he checked a mutiny, and after wintering in Corcyra, was succeeded early in 198 by Flamininus (Liv. 32.6.1-8; cf. Plut. Flam. 3.1-2; Zon. 9.16). On Villius, see Lübker, no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1939> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1939" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Spain (Liv. 28.45.10; 29.13.7; see 205-200). Returned to celebrate an ovatio (Liv. 31.20.1-7). See Degrassi 551." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1938> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1938" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Not Lentulus but Blasio (Liv. 33.27.1-2) was elected and sent to Spain at the end of 200 (cf. Liv. 31.50.11; and see 199, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1911> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1911" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Spain (Liv. 30.41.4-5; cf. 31.20.1). See above, on Cethegus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1886> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1886" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued (as Proconsul) in Spain (Liv. 30.27.9, and see 203, Promagistrates, cf. 30.41.4-5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1849> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1849" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued in Spain (Liv. 30.2.7; see 206 and 204, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1814> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1814" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Imperium prorogued as Proconsul in Spain (Liv. 29.13.7).{308}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1813> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1813" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 213, note 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1774> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1774" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued in Spain with imperium pro consule (Liv. 28.45.10; 29.13.7), where with his colleague Manlius Acidinus he quelled a revolt led by Indibilis and Mandonius (Liv. 29.2-3, and 13.7; App. Ib. 38).{303}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1773> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1773" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 213, note 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1770> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1770" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 29.11.12. Lucius was elected and held office while absent as Proconsul in Spain." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1749> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1749" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A private citizen invested with imperium pro consule to succeed Scipio in Spain (Liv. 28.38.1, pro praetore; cf. 29.13.7, pro consule; cf. Polyb. 11.33.8; Dio fr. 57.56; Zon. 9.11; Mommsen, Str. 2.652, note 4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1748> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1748" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 213, note 8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1512> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1512" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Cornelius Lentulus succeeded C. Papirius Maso. Liv. 25.2.2. The story that Scipio won election both for himself and his brother is intrinsically improbable, and despite the authority of Polybius, (10.4-5), has been generally rejected (E. Meyer, Kl. Schr. 2.430, note 4, and 431, note 1; Seidel 22f.). See 195, Aediles." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1511> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1511" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This Decemvir, who died in 173 (Liv. 42.10.6), is probably to be identified with one or other of two Cornelii Lentuli (nos. 187 and 188 in RE). The first of these was Praetor in 211, and Legate of Marcellus in 209, the other Curule Aedile in 205 and Consul in 199. Willems combines them in the person of one senator (1.311f.), but Bardt (4) questions the holding of a curule aedileship after the praetorship (see Seidel, 28, note 2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10037> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10037" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ovation ex Hispania. MRR I.324, III.63, Itgenshorst no. 164, Rich no. 163." .
